"""s56X — Triple-Play (IPTV/CATV + VoIP) profile + Public REST API hardening (Phase D)

Adds IPTV multicast VLAN profiles + VoIP/SIP profiles that can be attached
to ONUs. Pushes via the existing ONU OMCI/Telnet provisioning code path.

Tables (idempotent):
  * `iptv_profiles`         — company-scoped IPTV/CATV profile (mcast VLAN, IGMP version)
  * `voip_profiles`         — SIP server/credentials profile
  * `onu_iptv_assignments`  — many-to-many ONU ↔ IPTV profile
  * `onu_voip_assignments`  — many-to-many ONU ↔ VoIP profile

Plus, a tiny public REST gateway (with API-key auth) that wraps the most
common operations for downstream CRM integrations:

REST:
  GET  /api/admin/iptv-profiles
  POST /api/admin/iptv-profiles
  PATCH /api/admin/iptv-profiles/{id}
  DELETE /api/admin/iptv-profiles/{id}
  GET  /api/admin/voip-profiles
  POST /api/admin/voip-profiles
  PATCH /api/admin/voip-profiles/{id}
  DELETE /api/admin/voip-profiles/{id}
  POST /api/admin/onus/{onu_id}/iptv/{profile_id}/attach
  POST /api/admin/onus/{onu_id}/iptv/{profile_id}/detach
  POST /api/admin/onus/{onu_id}/voip/{profile_id}/attach
  POST /api/admin/onus/{onu_id}/voip/{profile_id}/detach

Public-API (with /api/v1/* prefix, X-API-Key auth from api_keys table):
  GET  /api/v1/onus?olt_id=&limit=
  GET  /api/v1/onus/{onu_id}
  POST /api/v1/onus/{onu_id}/reboot
  GET  /api/v1/customers/{customer_id}
"""
from __future__ import annotations

